Converting nan-values into mean and mode values¶

In [6]:
def ConNanToMeanAndMode():
    nan_cols_mode=["Gender","Married","Dependents","Self_Employed","Loan_Amount_Term","Credit_History"]
    for col in nan_cols_mode:
        df[col].fillna(df[col].mode()[0],inplace=True)
    df["LoanAmount"].fillna(df["LoanAmount"].mean(),inplace=True)
    #Converting '3+' value into '3' value in Dependents Column
    df["Dependents"].replace('3+','3',inplace=True)
    df['Loan_Status'].replace('N',0,inplace=True)
    df['Loan_Status'].replace('Y',1,inplace=True)
    uniqueValueOfDF()

remove outliers from ApplicantIncome and CoapplicantIncome columns¶

In [7]:
def outlier_removal(col,factor=1.5):
    import numpy as np
    X = col.copy()
    q1 = X.quantile(0.25)
    q3 = X.quantile(0.75)
    iqr = q3 - q1
    lower_bound = q1 - (factor * iqr)
    upper_bound = q3 + (factor * iqr)
    X.loc[((X < lower_bound) | (X > upper_bound))] = np.nan 
    avg_col=f'{X.mean():.1f}'
    avg_col=float(avg_col)
    #print(type(float(avg_col)))
    X=X.fillna(avg_col)
    #X.plot.box(figsize=(10, 9))
    return X
df['ApplicantIncome']=outlier_removal(df['ApplicantIncome'])
df['CoapplicantIncome']=outlier_removal(df['CoapplicantIncome'])

Training (Logistic Regression & SVM & KNN & Decision Tree & Gaussian Naive Bayes) Classifiers¶

we will use GridSearchCV for each classifier¶

which is exhaustive search over specified parameter values for an estimator¶

we will use StratifiedKFold¶

which provides train/test indices to split data in train/test sets.¶
and takes class information into account to avoid building folds with imbalanced class distributions (for binary or multiclass classification tasks).¶

we will use pipeline which implements utilities to build a composite estimator, as a chain of transforms and estimators¶

In [369]:
stratified_kfold = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=3,shuffle=True,random_state=11) 

Classifiers=["Logistic Regression","SVC","KNN","Decision Tree","GaussianNB"]

for classifier in Classifiers:
    
    param_grid = {}
    pipeline = Pipeline(steps=[])
    
    if classifier == "Logistic Regression":
        print("Logistic Regression Classifier\n")
        print("------------------------------")
        pipeline = Pipeline(steps = [['scaler', StandardScaler()], #  MinMaxScaler()
                                     ['lr', LogisticRegression(random_state=11,max_iter=1000)]])
        param_grid = {'lr__C':[0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 1, 10, 100, 1000]}
        
    if classifier == "SVC":
        print("SVC Classifier\n")
        print("--------------")
        pipeline = Pipeline(steps = [['scaler', StandardScaler()], #  MinMaxScaler()
                                     ['SVC', SVC(random_state=11)]])
        param_grid = {'SVC__kernel':('rbf', 'linear'), 'SVC__C':[1,2,3,5,10,15,20]}
    
    if classifier == "KNN":
        print("KNeighbors Classifier\n")
        print("----------------------")
        pipeline = Pipeline(steps = [['scaler', StandardScaler()], #  MinMaxScaler()
                                     ['KNN', KNeighborsClassifier()]])
        param_grid = [{'KNN__n_neighbors': [3, 5, 7, 9],'KNN__weights': ['uniform', 'distance'],'KNN__leaf_size': [15, 20]}]
        
    if classifier == "Decision Tree":
        print("Decision Tree Classifier\n")
        print("------------------------")
        pipeline = Pipeline(steps = [['scaler', StandardScaler()], #  MinMaxScaler()
                                     ['DT', DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='entropy',random_state=11)]])
        param_grid = {'DT__max_depth': (25,50,100,150, 155, 160),'DT__min_samples_split': (1, 2, 3),'DT__min_samples_leaf': (1, 2, 3)}
     
    if classifier == "GaussianNB":
        print("Gaussian Naive Bayes Classifier\n")
        print("-------------------------------")
        pipeline = Pipeline(steps = [['scaler', StandardScaler()], #  MinMaxScaler()
                                     ['GNB', GaussianNB()]])
        param_grid = {'GNB__priors': [None, [0.1,]* 2,],'GNB__var_smoothing': [1e-9, 1e-6, 1e-12],}
        
                                                                    
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator=pipeline,
                               param_grid=param_grid,
                               scoring='f1', #precision(important to avoid bankruptcy)/recall(important to avoid losing customers)/f1(chosed)/f1_micro/roc_auc 
                               cv=stratified_kfold,
                               n_jobs=-1)

    # training the current classifier
    grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    # Predictions of testing set
    y_grid_predictions=grid_search.predict(X_test)
    # Accuracy of testing set
    test_score = grid_search.score(X_test, y_test)
            
    best_estimator=grid_search.best_estimator_
    
    #Saving the current classifier with the best hyperparameters
    joblib.dump(best_estimator, "Classifiers/"+classifier+'.pkl')
    
    best_params=grid_search.best_params_
    cv_score = grid_search.best_score_
    print(f'Cross-validation Accuracy: {cv_score}\nTest Accuracy: {test_score}')
    print("param_grid: ",param_grid)
    print("best_estimator: ",best_estimator)
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_grid_predictions, target_names=['N','Y']))
    confusion = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_grid_predictions)
    df_cm = pd.DataFrame(confusion, index = ['N', 'Y'],columns = ['N', 'Y'])
    plt.figure(figsize = (5.5,4))
    sns.heatmap(df_cm, annot=True)
    plt.title('Logistic Regression\nAccuracy:{0:.3f}'.format(test_score))
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label');

    ## Plotting Precision-Recall Curve
    print("----------------------------------------")
    precision, recall, thresholds = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_grid_predictions)
    print("Plotting Precision-Recall Curve")
    print("-------------------------------")
    plt.figure()
    plt.xlim([0.0, 1.01])
    plt.ylim([0.0, 1.01])
    plt.plot(precision, recall, label='Precision-Recall Curve')
    plt.xlabel('Precision', fontsize=16)
    plt.ylabel('Recall', fontsize=16)
    plt.axes().set_aspect('equal')
    plt.show()
    print("----------------------------------------")

    ## Plotting roc_auc Curve
    print("Plotting roc Curve\n")
    print("------------------")
    fpr_lr, tpr_lr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_grid_predictions)
    roc_auc_lr = auc(fpr_lr, tpr_lr)
    print("roc_lr: ",roc_auc_lr)
    plt.figure()
    plt.xlim([-0.01, 1.00])
    plt.ylim([-0.01, 1.01])
    plt.plot(fpr_lr, tpr_lr, lw=3, label='LogRegr ROC curve (area = {:0.2f})'.format(roc_auc_lr))
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate', fontsize=16)
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate', fontsize=16)
    plt.title('ROC curve ', fontsize=16)
    plt.legend(loc='lower right', fontsize=13)
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='navy', lw=3, linestyle='--')
    plt.axes().set_aspect('equal')
    plt.show()
    print("---------------------------------------------------------------------------------")

def ConNexDataIntoOldFormat(z):
    temp_df=pd.DataFrame()
    newex=[]
    for eleind in range(len(z)):
        newex.append([])

        # Gender
        if z[eleind][0] == 0 :
            newex[eleind].append(1)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
        else:
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(1)

        # Married
        if z[eleind][1] == 0 :
            newex[eleind].append(1)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
        else:
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(1)

        # Dependents
        if z[eleind][2] == 0 :
            newex[eleind].append(1)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
        elif z[eleind][2] == 1:
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(1)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
        elif z[eleind][2] == 2:
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(1)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
        else:
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(1)

        #Education
        if z[eleind][3] == 1 :
            newex[eleind].append(1)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
        else:
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(1)

        #Self_Employed
        if z[eleind][4] == 0 :
            newex[eleind].append(1)
            newex[eleind].append(0)
        else:
            newex[eleind].append(0)
            newex[eleind].append(1)

        newex[eleind].append(z[eleind][5])
        newex[eleind].append(z[eleind][6])
        newex[eleind].append(z[eleind][7])
        newex[eleind].append(z[eleind][8])
        newex[eleind].append(z[eleind][9])
        
        new_row = {
                   "Gender_Female":newex[eleind][0],
                   "Gender_Male":newex[eleind][1],
                   "Married_No":newex[eleind][2],
                   "Married_Yes":newex[eleind][3],
                   "Dependents_0":newex[eleind][4],
                   "Dependents_1":newex[eleind][5],
                   "Dependents_2":newex[eleind][6],
                   "Dependents_3":newex[eleind][7],
                   "Education_Graduate":newex[eleind][8],
                   "Education_Not Graduate":newex[eleind][9],
                   "Self_Employed_No":newex[eleind][10],
                   "Self_Employed_Yes":newex[eleind][11],
                   "ApplicantIncome":newex[eleind][12],
                   "CoapplicantIncome":newex[eleind][13],
                   "LoanAmount":newex[eleind][14],
                   "Loan_Amount_Term":newex[eleind][15],
                   "Credit_History":newex[eleind][16]
                  }
        temp_df = temp_df.append(new_row, ignore_index=True)
    return temp_df

def predictResult(z,best_classifier_name):

    colus=["Gender","Married","Dependents","Education","Self_Employed"]
    new_test_data=ConNexDataIntoOldFormat(z)
    ordColus=["Gender_Female","Gender_Male","Married_No","Married_Yes","Dependents_0","Dependents_1","Dependents_2","Dependents_3","Education_Graduate","Education_Not Graduate","Self_Employed_No","Self_Employed_Yes","ApplicantIncome","CoapplicantIncome","LoanAmount","Loan_Amount_Term","Credit_History"]
    #Reordering the columns
    new_test_data=new_test_data[ordColus]
    #print(new_test_data.head())
    
    #Loading best Classifier
    best_classifier=joblib.load("Classifiers/"+best_classifier_name+'.pkl')
    
    #Predicting new Data using best model
    new_data_y=best_classifier.predict(new_test_data)
    for ele in new_data_y:
        if ele == 0:
            print("No")
        else:
            print("Yes")
